messages.content: What is the ComfyUI 3D Pose Editor node used for?
The 3D Pose Editor node is used to set pose ControlNet in ComfyUI.
What category does the ComfyUI 3D Pose Editor node belong to?
The ComfyUI 3D Pose Editor node belongs to the 'image/3D Pose Editor' category.
What problem might occur when using Efficient KSampler with the ComfyUI 3D Pose Editor?
The KSampler output may not change if the pose editor is used, as there might be a caching issue.
How can I add the workflow from the sample image to my ComfyUI?
You can add the workflow from the sample image by downloading the PNG file and dropping it into your ComfyUI.
What updates were made to the ComfyUI 3D Pose Editor on 2024.01.04?
On 2024.01.04, all the load methods were rewritten, and issues [#1], [#2], and [#4] were fixed. Credit is given to [@ltdrdata](https://github.com/ltdrdata) for their contributions.
How can I fix the non-responsive ComfyUI interface?
If your ComfyUI interface is not responding, you can try reloading your browser.
